# Lyx SDK Patterns

## Event Bus

```tsx
import { emit, on, useEvent } from "@lyx/sdk";

// Fire-and-forget event
emit("cart:add", { productId: "123" });

// Subscribe in a component (auto-cleanup)
useEvent("cart:add", (data) => {
  console.log("Added:", data.productId);
});

// Manual subscribe (remember to unsubscribe)
const unsub = on("cart:add", handler);
// later: unsub();
```

Event naming: `domain:action` (e.g. `cart:add`, `user:login`, `cat:theme`).

## Shared State

```tsx
import { useSharedState } from "@lyx/sdk";

const [user, setUser] = useSharedState("user", { name: "", loggedIn: false });
```

- Key must be unique across all MFEs
- Initial value only applied if key is not already set
- All MFEs sharing the same key see updates instantly

## Navigation

```tsx
import { navigate } from "@lyx/sdk";

navigate("dashboard");           // navigate within the app
navigate("settings", "main");    // target a specific slot
```

## Dynamic MFE Loading

```tsx
import { MFELoader } from "@lyx/sdk";

<MFELoader name="contact-form" fallback={<p>Loading...</p>} />
```

## Anti-patterns

- Never use `window.postMessage` — use `emit`/`on`
- Never import from another MFE directly — use events or shared state
- Never hardcode URLs — use SDK config
